Assist-2-Sell is a real estate franchise organization in the United States and Canada. It was founded in 1987 by Mary LaMeres-Pomin and Lyle E. Martin and is based in Reno, NV.
As of May 2011, the Assist-2-Sell network consisted of approximately 300 offices in 44 U.S. states and 5 Canadian provinces.
The company describes itself as a full-service discount real estate company. Franchise owners/brokers and their agents provide home sellers and home buyers with full brokerage services. Home sellers pay a flat fee once their home is sold, instead of a commission that is a percentage of a home's sale price.


